narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this section to any freshman who wants to improve their academic writing ability.

Yes, I would definitely recommend this class. It's a really good way to become a more critical reader and a better argumentative writer, and it will change how you evaluate your own, and others', writing.

English 114 is a class in which you analyze documents, construct arguments, find tensions in other's arguments, and really understand how to logically structure a paper. You look at structure, scope, argument, and archive. I would recommend it this class to anyone. Even if you are able to take 120, like I was, you should take this class because it really allows you to delve into argument analysis. Also, you may be able to get an article published!

It's a great english course where you become a more critical reader and writer. After this course, you are able to more easily identify problems within a work, and you become better at elaborating on this problem. I would definitely recommend this course to another student. The topic is interesting and not like a typical English class.
Very fun class because the topics are always relevant and forceful. If you need to fulfill a distributional requirement, this is definitely the class to take.
This course is great for those that need a writing credit. I would definitely recommend it for anyone needing a writing credit and wants to take an English course
It is a good introduction to college writing, so I would recommend it.
Yes I would recommend this course for anyone seeking to improve his or her writing skills.
A look at debates across cultures and disciplines that will change your perspective in ways you could never imagine.
